I can understand and appreciate these lines of criticism. I felt the voice itself needed to seem a bit stilted and carry shades of not-actually-caring-beyond-a-superficial-level and for its own purposes, yet still say some of what a person who feels deprived of social interaction could appreciate. Excluding Research Assistant NoNameGiven's precise responses, actions, and terminal commands was deliberate. I didn't want to push the apathy too much more than was done because it had the potential to come off as some sort of compulsion/mind-control effect, which it definitely should not be. Similar point on people having different reactions once they were about to disappear; people have different personalities and universal happiness felt like it would be a compulsion. YMMV on all of the above's execution is perfectly valid though.







